item.title: The Nights
item.description: Hey, once upon a younger year When all our shadows disappeared The animals inside came out to play Hey, when face to face with all our fears Learned our lessons through the tears Made memories we knew would never fade One day my fatherâ€”he told me, “Son, don’t let it slip away” He took me in his arms, I heard him say, “When you get older Your wild life will live for younger days
